AB  - Few-shot semantic segmentation techniques can effectively alleviate the high data costs associated with industrial applications. The task of metal surface defect segmentation, due to the numerous types of defects and limited data availability, is highly suited for the application of few-shot semantic segmentation techniques. However, current methods for handling multiple defects in support images may result in semantic shifts in the global prototype due to mask average pooling (MAP). In this paper, we propose the Multiple Prototype Guided Enhanced Network (MPENet). We propose a multiple prototype mask average mask pooling (Multi-MAP) operation to extract each defect region as a prototype and guidance enhancement module to leverage these multiple prototypes to enhance the global prototype. The final experimental results demonstrate that MPENet can achieves state-of-the-art performance on the FSSD12 dataset with minimal increase in learnable parameters.  © 2024 IEEE.
